<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-07-25T11:16:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-07-25T11:16:00-05:00" n="11" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d11">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.3335/26</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Buenos Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-25T12:00:00-04:16">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 25, 1917, noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Fleet escorted by Argentine squadron delayed 3 hours by fog, arrived
                            safely in the north basin at sunset. Crowd estimated at two hundred
                            thousand received them. Minister for Foreign Affairs gave a private
                            welcome dinner: guests Vice President, Minister of Marine, Papal Nuncio,
                            Spanish Ambassador, Mayor of City, Presidents Jockey Club and Reception
                            Committee and ladies.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>